Class BookEntry

java.lang.Object
BookEntry
public final class BookEntry
extends java.lang.Object
Immutable class encapsulating data for a single book entry.

  • Constructor Details

    • BookEntry

      public BookEntry​(java.lang.String name, java.lang.String[] authors, float rating, java.lang.String ISBN, int pages)
      Constructor of the class BookEntry that is used to Initialize all the private fields of the class.
      Parameters:
      name - String that contains the title of the book.
      authors - Array of Strings that contains all the information regarding the author(s) of the book.
      rating - Float that describes the rating of the book, must be within the accepted range (between 0 and 5).
      ISBN - String that describes the ISBN number of the book.
      pages - int that describes the number of pages of the book.
      Throws:
      java.lang.NullPointerException - if a member of the parameter authors is null or if the parameters name or ISBN are null
      java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the rating is not within the accepted range, uses the method checkRating for it.
